Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.16,0:00:13.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's skip training today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.58,0:00:16.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were hurt pretty badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.84,0:00:19.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, my injuries pose no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.88,0:00:23.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am more concerned about you, \NShirou. Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.72,0:00:26.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.55,0:00:30.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you are in pain, do not hesitate to speak up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.73,0:00:31.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.16,0:02:28.54,Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(276,559)}#11 A Visitor Approaches Lightly
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.27,0:02:40.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's a relief... The pain is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.91,0:02:51.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday was pretty rough, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.58,0:02:57.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll make breakfast as thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.96,0:03:03.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.05,0:03:17.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kuzuki-sensei has called in sick today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.85,0:03:19.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? Kuzuki-sensei did?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.58,0:03:20.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it supposed to snow today?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.98,0:03:22.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sweet! Study hall!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.60,0:03:23.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Settle down, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.27,0:03:26.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know that normally, this is \Nyour World History class,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.82,0:03:31.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but since I'm here, let's have an English pop quiz!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.07,0:03:33.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No quizzes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.40,0:03:34.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tyrant!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.70,0:03:35.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Taiga!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.12,0:03:37.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.20,0:03:41.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I make last period on Saturday study \Nhall, it'll just turn into playtime!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.87,0:03:45.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So graciously accept your teacher's kindness!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.14,0:03:54.97,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,School has now ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.22,0:03:58.60,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Students are not permitted to remain \Non campus after school hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.60,0:04:00.72,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please leave immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.48,0:04:04.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should I be worried?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.94,0:04:07.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My arm's numb, but somehow, it feels heavier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.65,0:04:12.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to talk to Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.72,0:04:18.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if she didn't come to me, I doubt \Nthere were any major developments.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.25,0:04:25.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm home late.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.79,0:04:28.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have lunch ready in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.59,0:04:33.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.80,0:04:37.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's the first time I've ever broken a dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.81,0:04:41.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I'll clean it up right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.10,0:04:43.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it. Just sit at the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.23,0:04:46.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You must be fatigued, Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.27,0:04:50.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. I will clean it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.36,0:04:54.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I am tired... Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.33,0:05:00.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.13,0:05:12.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,T-Tohsaka? What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.59,0:05:15.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here because you stood me \Nup at our regular check-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.76,0:05:17.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stood you up?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.22,0:05:20.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I admit that I forgot to meet you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.77,0:05:23.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But did we agree on regular check-ins?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.52,0:05:28.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! I apologize for forgetting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.15,0:05:31.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As your partner, I should check \Nin with you regularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.57,0:05:34.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's use this opportunity to \Nhold our meeting here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.36,0:05:38.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, we were just about to have lunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.41,0:05:39.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.87,0:05:41.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't had lunch yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.89,0:05:43.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so I'll join you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.33,0:05:46.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, not so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.86,0:05:57.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So in the end, our only option against \NCaster is to resort to using force.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.92,0:05:59.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.55,0:06:03.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is a powerful barrier against spiritual \Nbeings erected around that mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.50,0:06:05.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The front gate is the only way in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.81,0:06:10.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So if we force our way onto the \Ntemple grounds, Caster will be waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.19,0:06:12.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.11,0:06:15.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, why are you sitting so far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.86,0:06:19.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because you poached my usual place!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.20,0:06:26.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, once we're on the grounds, \Nthe question is how we'll corner Caster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.16,0:06:29.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we play our cards wrong, she might \Ntake out all of Ryuudou Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.91,0:06:32.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,True, that is something Caster could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.75,0:06:35.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber, don't say scary stuff like that so casually!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.66,0:06:38.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that Caster will \Nself-destruct if we corner her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.08,0:06:40.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's likely, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.89,0:06:42.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe she would.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.85,0:06:48.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You two are totally in sync...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.69,0:06:53.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, it's this late already?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.61,0:06:56.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we should wrap things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.49,0:06:59.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get dinner started.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.82,0:07:03.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Emiya-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.24,0:07:05.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you staring at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.36,0:07:07.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I was just...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.55,0:07:10.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.00,0:07:13.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In public, we're fellow Masters, \Nso I don't bother you there,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.42,0:07:15.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but inside your own home,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.03,0:07:17.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you revert to your natural instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.80,0:07:21.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a guy, so it's a perfectly ordinary reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.80,0:07:23.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it's odd, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.43,0:07:25.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber is a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.31,0:07:29.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And from what I hear, Fujimura-sensei \Nand Sakura are always coming over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.73,0:07:32.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't be any different.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.48,0:07:34.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, just go home, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.48,0:07:39.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? How can I go home, when we've \Nyet to settle on a strategy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.53,0:07:42.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou, Rin's point is valid, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:46.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see no issue with her staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.29,0:07:49.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you start, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.62,0:07:51.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.17,0:07:55.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Fuji-nee... Fujimura-sensei will \Nprobably show up later,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.04,0:07:57.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so you'll have to persuade her yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.63,0:07:59.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.67,0:08:02.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know all about Fujimura-sensei, \Nso don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.10,0:08:06.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame me if this blows up in your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.64,0:08:11.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.02,0:08:12.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.14,0:08:13.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, it's cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.90,0:08:15.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's gonna snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.40,0:08:18.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you're making a hot pot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.82,0:08:20.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's my Shirou!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.30,0:08:20.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're freezing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.65,0:08:21.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you're awake now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.86,0:08:23.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.07,0:08:24.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm working over a fire here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.72,0:08:25.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever... Hurry, hurry, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.99,0:08:30.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hot pot! Hot pot! Hot pot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.08,0:08:28.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, get off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.87,0:08:33.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you don't mind my \Njoining you, Fujimura-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.08,0:08:35.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why, it's Tohsaka-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.63,0:08:39.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's unusual to run into you \Nat Shirou's place... Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.01,0:08:43.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing at Shirou's place?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.34,0:08:46.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, Tohsaka-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.30,0:08:48.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.22,0:08:50.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is thoughtless of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.14,0:08:51.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What am I doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.52,0:08:55.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm being treated to dinner at Emiya-kun's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.52,0:08:57.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's far more thoughtless
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.69,0:09:01.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of you to barge in without even \Nringing the doorbell, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.60,0:09:06.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm the household chaperone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.24,0:09:09.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was left in charge by Emiya-kun's father,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.33,0:09:11.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so we're practically family!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.07,0:09:12.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.79,0:09:15.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After dinner, Emiya-kun and \NI will be studying for a test,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.83,0:09:17.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so don't mind us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.11,0:09:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.88,0:09:20.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou? I mean, Emiya-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.42,0:09:22.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.26,0:09:26.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it's difficult to address him formally, \Ndon't push yourself to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.09,0:09:30.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What you call Emiya-kun is none of my concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.27,0:09:34.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka-san, did you hear about \Nthis from Sakura-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.89,0:09:36.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.23,0:09:41.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, anything that Matou-san told \Nme must be treated as confidential.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.69,0:09:45.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I hope it's exactly as you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.70,0:09:48.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Game, set, and match.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.87,0:09:53.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave these here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.45,0:09:54.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.75,0:09:56.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I do the dishes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.92,0:09:59.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be fair if I do nothing in return for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.75,0:10:01.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, just owe me one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.40,0:10:21.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fujimura-sensei, is Emiya-kun always this clumsy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.77,0:10:26.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No way. As long as I've known \Nhim, he's never broken a dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.15,0:10:30.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I bet he's self-conscious because you're here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.62,0:10:32.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As a foreign invader, naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.58,0:10:37.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.67,0:10:40.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take it from here, so go get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.13,0:10:41.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.42,0:10:44.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've got this, so go drink some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:50.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you shouldn't help?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.64,0:10:53.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You asked her over, and if you leave \Nher alone, she's gonna hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.97,0:10:56.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Why are you reading too \Nfar into this, you idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.64,0:10:58.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't invite her over!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.89,0:11:03.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And anyway, I don't really \Ncare if Tohsaka hates me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.16,0:11:13.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.03,0:11:16.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe she went out into the courtyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.87,0:11:18.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The courtyard?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.99,0:11:25.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.56,0:11:28.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I like your Bounded Field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.97,0:11:35.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the one at my house, you can \Nsense human emotion in this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.02,0:11:40.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Care to join me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.40,0:11:50.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.24,0:11:52.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was just curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.70,0:11:54.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This house is unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.83,0:11:59.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It occurred to me that maybe you're \Nbetter off the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.25,0:12:02.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A hopeless amateur, you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.29,0:12:06.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean it that way, \Nbut maybe that's exactly it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.38,0:12:10.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what Emiya Kiritsugu was like as a mage,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.34,0:12:13.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but this compound is incredibly natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.59,0:12:16.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For a mage's workshop, it's quite open.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.47,0:12:19.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's like you're welcome to come and go freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.77,0:12:22.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't like that at your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.48,0:12:24.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.40,0:12:28.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It tries to keep people out, but once \Nyou're in, it doesn't let you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.32,0:12:35.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At times, I think it's wrong, but it \Nisn't something I can change.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.95,0:12:39.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I like it the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.00,0:12:43.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was probably chosen as the heir \Nbecause my personality is this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.00,0:12:47.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was it hard for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.88,0:12:49.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Training to be a mage?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.88,0:12:53.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to say, but I never found it hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.72,0:12:57.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, learning new things was fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.35,0:13:01.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I just tell you? That's how I'm wired.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.73,0:13:05.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So if you're worried about me, it's misplaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.94,0:13:08.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.98,0:13:10.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then why are you at school?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.65,0:13:13.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to live a mage's \Nlife, isn't it sort of pointless?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.99,0:13:16.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It may be a detour, but it's not pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.82,0:13:18.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's fun to be a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.08,0:13:22.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And at heart, I'm a hedonist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.79,0:13:25.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Succeeding my father is my duty,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.33,0:13:27.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but I wouldn't do it if I didn't enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.50,0:13:32.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even the reason for my partnership with \Nyou is because you're interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.59,0:13:33.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.84,0:13:35.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm glad you're having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.14,0:13:37.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.64,0:13:41.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And? It's been fun for you, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.39,0:13:45.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't you saying anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.69,0:13:47.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.07,0:13:54.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a straight answer, Emiya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.28,0:13:57.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because I might have completely misunderstood you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.99,0:14:03.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I never thought of mage training as fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.79,0:14:05.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even magic itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.12,0:14:10.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if the people around me \Nwere happy, I was happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.21,0:14:17.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So if I studied magic, I might be able \Nto help someone someday...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.97,0:14:21.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to be a hero of justice, \Njust like Kiritsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.60,0:14:23.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I studied magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.14,0:14:27.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, that's my reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.44,0:14:31.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So then, you didn't study magic for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.57,0:14:35.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.78,0:14:39.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because it makes me happy \Nto be useful to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.41,0:14:43.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, that's just being happy, not having fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.04,0:14:47.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, what I'm asking is if you personally enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.87,0:14:49.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about others,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.50,0:14:52.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking if there's anything about \Nmagic that you consider fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.71,0:14:56.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to say if I personally enjoy it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.22,0:15:04.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I sort of feel like I don't deserve more wishes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.56,0:15:05.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.43,0:15:06.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a straight answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.85,0:15:08.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I guess I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.06,0:15:12.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm so angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.56,0:15:13.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So basically,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.94,0:15:17.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you're always worrying about others, \Nbut never focusing on yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.03,0:15:18.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, hey—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.03,0:15:19.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! No backtalk!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.03,0:15:25.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I always thought you were similar, \Nbut I never imagined you were {\i1}this{\i0} alike!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.33,0:15:27.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Tohsaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.96,0:15:30.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.21,0:15:33.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm angry because you don't get why I'm angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.84,0:15:36.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right. That settles it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.42,0:15:41.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow, I'll make you admit defeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.34,0:15:43.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to go back to chasing me around?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.80,0:15:44.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.18,0:15:48.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you a taste of something \Nspecial I've been saving!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.11,0:15:55.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.23,0:15:58.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're going home, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.40,0:15:59.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll walk you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.86,0:16:01.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.41,0:16:07.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Enough with the "Tohsaka, Tohsaka"!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.83,0:16:09.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka, what are you wearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.04,0:16:13.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I spoke to Archer and had him \Nbring me an overnight bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.21,0:16:17.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I got Fujimura-sensei's permission, so it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.30,0:16:21.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use the guest room on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.10,0:16:32.73,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trace on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.52,0:16:36.82,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tracing fundamental structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.82,0:16:39.61,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Strengthening component materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.41,0:16:49.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,More magic training tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.33,0:16:54.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Kiritsugu taught me to never miss a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.00,0:16:58.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess that was the only thing \NI really learned from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.88,0:17:01.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Only that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.67,0:17:06.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He taught you nothing of the wisdom \Nor behavior expected of mages?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.68,0:17:08.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No... After all,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.51,0:17:12.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the guy who was supposed to teach me \Nwasn't really like a mage himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.14,0:17:13.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was a poor excuse for an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.35,0:17:17.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He'd say that if you're going to enjoy \Nsomething, enjoy it to the fullest,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.82,0:17:19.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then he'd play around like a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.44,0:17:24.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. You enjoyed having \Nsuch a master, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.86,0:17:27.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I looked up to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.03,0:17:29.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was carefree and nothing like a mage,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.70,0:17:33.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but to me, Kiritsugu was a true magic-user.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.43,0:17:37.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.92,0:17:40.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is wrong with your left side?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.01,0:17:44.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You noticed, Saber?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.05,0:17:45.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.43,0:17:48.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a little numb.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.89,0:17:51.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't slowing me down at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.97,0:17:53.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then the cause is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.02,0:17:57.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I think it's a reaction to the \Nprojection magic I did last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.77,0:18:02.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is most of your body still numb?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.69,0:18:03.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.90,0:18:05.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's hardly surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.74,0:18:08.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.78,0:18:11.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we had a non-aggression pact.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.19,0:18:14.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.16,0:18:17.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you come any closer, you must \Nbe prepared for the consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.04,0:18:20.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Saber. He doesn't want to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.92,0:18:21.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But he...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.71,0:18:22.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.92,0:18:25.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.55,0:18:28.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing you, you didn't drop by to say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.10,0:18:33.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rin told me that you performed a \Nprojection, and it really is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.47,0:18:39.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have no sensation in half your body, \Nand your center of gravity is 7 cm off, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.81,0:18:43.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I might be of some assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.36,0:18:50.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're fortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.03,0:18:52.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I expected to see necrosis,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.03,0:18:53.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but something that was \Nclosed has been opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.70,0:18:56.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Something that was closed has been opened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.54,0:19:01.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Circuits you were meant to use from the \Nbeginning had grown dormant from neglect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.13,0:19:04.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The numbness is only temporary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.63,0:19:08.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By suddenly flooding circuits you never \Nused with mana at full power,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.30,0:19:12.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you sent them into a state of shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.64,0:19:15.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This means that the circuits have \Nreturned to an active state.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.80,0:19:23.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.65,0:19:27.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll recover in a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.32,0:19:29.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you can move properly again,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.91,0:19:32.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you should be a better mage than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.16,0:19:36.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You certainly know a lot about this, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.83,0:19:39.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I went through something similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.08,0:19:41.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I lost the use of one arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.13,0:19:45.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.38,0:19:47.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.30,0:19:52.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.76,0:19:54.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Let your ideals drag you to your death."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.97,0:19:57.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.77,0:19:59.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It seems self-explanatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.52,0:20:01.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to add.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.44,0:20:05.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then what the hell are you fighting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.23,0:20:10.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's obvious. My reason for \Nfighting is simply for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.65,0:20:12.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.20,0:20:14.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.37,0:20:18.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If your desire is to fulfill the \Nideal of not hurting anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.33,0:20:20.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then do as you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.04,0:20:23.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But only if that desire is truly yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.50,0:20:27.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you fight of your own free will,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.84,0:20:31.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,any resulting crime or punishment \Nis of your own making.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.59,0:20:33.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Accepting them is a part of that ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.18,0:20:37.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if that desire was borrowed from another,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.60,0:20:40.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the ideals you uphold are mere fantasies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.31,0:20:43.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There must be a reason for fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.56,0:20:46.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that reason must never be an ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.23,0:20:50.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you fight for an ideal, you can only save ideals.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.70,0:20:54.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't entail helping others.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.82,0:20:59.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A reason to fight is the desire to save something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.75,0:21:03.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, it is for you. \NRight, Emiya Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.79,0:21:08.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But salvation by the hands \Nof another is not salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.00,0:21:11.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Such salvation is like money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.55,0:21:13.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When used, it passes into another's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.47,0:21:18.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that you can probably achieve \Nyour wish to save others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.81,0:21:23.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no hope of saving yourself in doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.10,0:21:29.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You will repeat the cycle until you die, \Nstill clinging to ideals that are not your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.15,0:21:35.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is why your ideals are meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.49,0:21:39.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing comes of helping others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.91,0:21:43.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, you can save neither \Nothers nor yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.04,0:21:46.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A lie of a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.09,0:21:50.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.92,0:21:54.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't true.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.85,0:23:28.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to go to such \Nextremes to help others!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.94,0:23:30.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You truly are a foolish child!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.81,0:23:33.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You still have no stomach for brutality, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.44,0:23:36.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I promised myself that I'd fight \Nto stop people like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.61,0:23:39.99,Next,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(515,1)}Next Time \NThe Final Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.65,0:23:39.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Run, Shirou!
